main event: Two young observers saw a bright object in the woods near Ft. Pierce, Florida, on March 23, 1966, initially thinking it was a rocket but later believing it to be a balloon that blew up when they approached it.
interesting points: The observers thought the object was a rocket at first,The object became so bright that the witnesses couldn't look at it,They believed it was hovering before they found it on the ground, The object burst when they got close, The witnesses called the Palm Beach airport to inquire about balloon launches but were told none had occurred in the past two weeks.
sighted object: a bright object thought to be a balloon
witness description: two young observers who were on their way to Scouts
